    "description": "If you're a passionate Risk Analyst with drive and ambition, Acuite Ratings Holdings Services in Varanasi is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Acuite Ratings Holdings Services:\nAcuite Ratings Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n• Maintain general ledger and ensure accurate bookkeeping\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Manage credit risk assessment and loan appraisal processes\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Ed / M.Ed from a recognized institution\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Due Diligence\n• Proficiency in Budgeting\n• Proficiency in IFRS\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Referral bonus program\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Learning & development budget\n• Flexible working hours\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Acuite Ratings Holdings Services!",
